#compdef imsearch
# =============================================================================
# imsearch — large-scale similar-image search via local feature-point
#            matching (OpenCV ORB descriptors + FAISS HNSW indexing).
#            Build a searchable database from millions of images, find
#            near-duplicates or visually similar images in milliseconds.
#            Combines OpenCV's ORB keypoint extraction (orientation-
#            invariant 256-bit binary descriptors), FAISS's k-nearest-
#            neighbor index (HNSW or IVF), perceptual dHash for fast
#            pre-filtering, and BLAKE3 for deduplication-key hashing.
#            Supports CLI single-shot queries AND an HTTP server mode
#            (axum) with multipart image upload + Bearer-token auth.
#            Optimized for x86 SIMD (AVX-512, AVX2, SSE4.2) and runs
#            faiss's quantization + clustering kernels directly.
#            Designed by lolishinshi for large image collections —
#            "数千万级别" (tens-of-millions-scale) image search.
#
# Author:  lolishinshi (Chinese-language Rust developer; primary
#          maintainer; project tagline is in Mandarin Chinese
#          "基于特征点匹配的大规模相似图片搜索")
# Source:  https://github.com/lolishinshi/imsearch
# CLI:     src/main.rs + src/config.rs + src/cli/ (uses clap-derive
#                                                  for argv +
#                                                  console-rs/indicatif
#                                                  for progress bars)
# Library: console-rs/indicatif
#          ("A command line progress reporting library for Rust" —
#           the CANONICAL Rust progress-bar library, by the console-rs
#           org which also publishes `console` and `dialoguer`)
# License: Apache-2.0 / MIT
# Status:  Active — 1024+ stars on lolishinshi/imsearch; production-
#          deployed in Chinese-language image-search SaaS;
#          indicatif itself is 5153+ stars and the de-facto Rust
#          progress library.
#
